            {
              "id": "2f2f8a9",
              "elType": "widget",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Spraying water is also quite inefficient because of the loss of water through natural processes, like evaporation, which pushes to irrigate when the sun is not very strong, early in the morning or late in the day. But the most important loss of water occurs through soil infiltration, which is normal, because we don’t want the soil to retain too much water, but causes a great inefficiency in water distribution. </span></p>",
                "align": "center",
                "_margin": {
                  "unit": "px",
                  "top": "10",
